22/02/2004
BERLIN, Germany -- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder praised the reforms made by the incumbent Turkish government on Saturday (21 February), saying that they have helped the country make a serious progress on the road towards EU membership.But he also stressed the necessity of resolving the Cyprus issue. The chancellor's comments came ahead of his visit to Turkey which will take place 22 February to 24 February, at the invitation of Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan. (Anadolu Agency - 21/02/04)
